    "choking": {
      "title": "Choking Child",
      "tabs": [
        {
          "id": "overview",
          "label": "Overview"
        },
        {
          "id": "notes",
          "label": "Notes"
        }
      ],
      "drugsCards": [],
      "notesMarkdown": "### Recognition\n\nSudden onset of respiratory distress with history of eating or playing with small objects.\n\n### Effective vs Ineffective Cough\n\n- Effective: Able to speak, cry, cough forcefully\n- Ineffective: Unable to vocalize, silent cough, cyanosis, decreasing consciousness\n\n### Important Notes\n\nNever perform blind finger sweeps. Only remove visible objects that are easily accessible. Do not give abdominal thrusts to infants under 1 year.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "choke_1",
          "type": "header",
          "color": "green",
          "text": "Suspect foreign body airway obstruction",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "choke_2",
          "type": "step",
          "color": "grey",
          "text": "Shout for HELP",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "choke_3",
          "type": "header",
          "color": "blue",
          "text": "Cough effective?",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "choke_4",
          "type": "branch",
          "question": "Choose",
          "options": [
            {
              "label": "NO",
              "to": "choke_no",
              "color": "red"
            },
            {
              "label": "YES",
              "to": "choke_yes",
              "color": "green"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "choke_no",
          "type": "step",
          "color": "red",
          "text": "Ineffective cough • Back blows & chest thrusts (infant) or abdominal thrusts (child >1yr)",
          "icon": "camera",
          "image": {
            "url": "./assets/images/choking_ref.svg",
            "caption": "Choking management techniques"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "choke_yes",
          "type": "step",
          "color": "green",
          "text": "Encourage cough • Continue to check for deterioration",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        }
      ]
    },
    "newborn_ls": {
      "title": "Newborn Life Support",
      "tabs": [
        {
          "id": "overview",
          "label": "Overview"
        },
        {
          "id": "notes",
          "label": "Notes"
        }
      ],
      "drugsCards": [],
      "notesMarkdown": "### Initial Assessment (Golden Minute)\n\n- Assess immediately: tone, breathing, heart rate\n- Most newborns establish breathing spontaneously\n- Only ~10% need some assistance\n- <1% need extensive resuscitation\n\n### Temperature Management\n\nMaintain temperature 36.5-37.5°C. Use plastic wrap for very preterm infants (<28 weeks). Avoid hyperthermia.\n\n### Oxygen Titration\n\nStart with air for term/near-term newborns. Use SpO₂ monitoring. Titrate oxygen to target saturations.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "nb_1",
          "type": "pill",
          "text": "(Antenatal counselling) Team briefing and equipment check"
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_2",
          "type": "header",
          "color": "maroon",
          "text": "Birth • Delay cord clamping if possible",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_3",
          "type": "step",
          "color": "grey",
          "text": "Start clock / note time • Dry / wrap, stimulate, keep warm",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_4",
          "type": "header",
          "color": "blue",
          "text": "Assess • Colour, tone, breathing, heart rate",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_5",
          "type": "pill",
          "text": "Ensure an open airway • Preterm: consider CPAP"
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_6",
          "type": "step",
          "color": "peach",
          "text": "If gasping / not breathing: Give 5 inflations (30 cm H₂O) • Apply PEEP 5–6 cm H₂O • Apply SpO₂ +/- ECG",
          "icon": "camera",
          "image": {
            "url": "./assets/images/newborn_ref.svg",
            "caption": "Newborn life support initial assessment"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "nb_7",
          "type": "header",
          "color": "blue",
          "text": "Reassess • If no increase in heart rate, look for chest movement",
          "icon": "clipboard"
        }
      ]
    }
